						               													<description>A Strategy Game for Enlightened Minds&amp;#10;&amp;#10;For over 1,000 years, Tibet's Potala Palace has been a center of knowledge, meditation and peace. As the seat of the Tibetan government, Potala has been the home of Dalai Lamas, Tibetan Kings and countless generations of Buddhist monks.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Deep within the Palace is a Secret Garden where Buddhist Elders bring student monks to test them in the arts of focus, meditation and concentration. On the floor of the garden is etched a grid of 312 squares. Here, 2-4 students at a time are challenged to place colored stones on the grid, with the ultimate goal of placing more stones than the others. Their work is guided by two deceptively simple rules...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;In addition, as the stones are placed, an Elder walks silently around the perimeter of the garden, keeping a tally of all he sees...&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Online Play&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;     Cycloops (turn-based)&amp;#10;&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
